-- Saudi oil minister says will meet customers' needs
-- 
-- Tue May 8, 2012 3:07am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/08/us-saudi-output-customers-idUSBRE8470A220120508

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Top oil exporter Saudi Arabia will satisfy its customers needs whatever they are, Oil Minister Ali al-Naimi said on Tuesday. 
 Naimi, on a visit to Tokyo, was asked if Saudi Arabia has increased its oil supply to Japan. He told reporters: "You have to ask the Japanese." He added, "We will always satisfy our customers requests, whatever the request is." (Reporting by Osamu Tsukimori)